Dane

Korean: 데인

Hometown:

Seoul

Country:

South Korea

Introduction

Dane is a South Korean singer-songwriter who debuted on October 10, 2024, with his single "Selfie." The song, characterized by its minimalist arrangement featuring just vocals and guitar, delves into themes of post-breakup emotions and longing. Dane drew inspiration from personal experiences, aiming to create a relatable narrative for listeners.
​
Prior to his solo career, Dane was a trainee at Kakao Entertainment. He decided to pursue a path as a singer-songwriter, leading to his collaboration with producer BOYTOY, known for working with artists like Jackson Wang and (G)I-DLE. This partnership culminated in the production of "Selfie."

Dane's musical style is influenced by artists such as Daniel Caesar, whose song "Get You" profoundly impacted him and steered his interest towards the R&B genre. He aspires to deliver genuine and heartfelt music, focusing on simplicity to highlight the emotional depth of his songs.
